General Surgery Registrar Job - Singapore
Earn up to $120K per annum
Largest public hospital in northern Singapore
Live and work in Singapore
Singapore
General Surgery Registrar positions are available at a large tertiary facility located in northern Singapore.
Our client is the largest public hospital in the northern part of Singapore with specialist outpatient clinics, acute care and emergency centre and inpatient wards build to serve the healthcare needs of the community. It seeks to provide high quality, affordable and hassle free healthcare with science, love and wisdom. Its future plans include the establishment of a new community hospital and a medical centre.
Brimming with a harmonious blend of culture, cuisine, arts and architecture, Singapore is a location that’s rich in contrast and colour. Singapore thrives on innovation making it one of the coolest destinations in Asia. Hotels are fabulous, the dining superlative and the cocktails served at the myriad of roof-top bars are the talk of the region. The city is safe, clean and easy to navigate. Do as much or as little as you like – with beautiful gardens to explore, world class shopping and plenty of man-made attractions there is something for everyone.
Seniority:
Registrar/ SpR
Specialty: General Surgery
